.\"Modified from man(1) of FreeBSD, the NetBSD mdoc.template, and mdoc.samples.
.Dd 12/01/21
.Dt hsh(1)
.Os Ubuntu
.Sh NAME
.Nm hsh
- recreated UNIX command line interpreter
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
sh

.Sh DESCRIPTION
The hsh utility displays a prompt ($ ) for the user and waits for input.
 It then reads user input and executes the appropriate commands if it exists within the PATH.
 It will also interpret built-ins "exit" and "env".
.Pp

.Sh EXAMPLES
.Pp
1. Interactive:
.Pp
hsh$ ls
example.c helloworld.c main.h
.Pp
2. Non-Interactive:
sh$ ls | ./hsh
exmple.c helloworld.c main.h
.Pp
